headline: Hedge funds bet against power and pile into materials, says Goldman Sachs
summary: Global hedge funds sold U.S. electric and water utilities stocks at the fastest pace in two months while buying U.S. materials stocks such as chemicals, metals and mining as well as paper and forest shares in the week to Friday, Goldman Sachs said.  U.S. utilities shares are now among the most sold U.S. stock sectors in November, showed a note from Goldman Sachs prime brokerage sent to investors on Friday and seen by Reuters on Monday.
